manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Eye-Catching Aesthetic The perfect combination of eye-catching design aesthetic, proprietary feature innovation and one of the most versatile packing functionalities Samsonite has ever created, the Stryde 2 is a true robust yet approachable luggage collection that can’t be missed.
Interior Features These carry-ons feature a USB port for powering up to stay connected, an organized interior with built-in pockets, and a versatile snap-in packing cube.

RightHeight Handle System The RightHeight handle system features multiple 1” adjustments and an ergonomically designed comfort grip for a customizable trip. Wheels The patented Off-Set Tru-Trac GT wheel system features multi-layer tire technology for dampening vibration, and a V-shaped design that provides stability with a smooth and responsive glide. USB Charging Port Stay connected wherever you go with the built in USB charging port.

How to Use the TSA Combination Lock Our TSA-approved combination locks are simple and easy to use, no key required! Use a ballpoint pen or other pointed object to press the small button located near the dials. With the button pressed in, set the dials to your desired code, and slide the button with the key hole towards to the dials to set. The code is now ready to use. The key hole is intended only for use by TSA agents, and no keys are included or required to use our TSA combination locks. The factory default code for new luggage is 0-0-0.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Light, solid, stable, fits under NY Subway turnstiles
reviews.reviewText: Purchased 2 of these (Samsonite Stryde Hardside Glider Medium Journey, Blue Slate) as my 1st "hardshell" bags for international travel. This review is written after 9 months and 3 international tripsPart of the attraction being that they are quite distinctive and easily recognized on the carousel. Despite their unusual dimensions they still fit a full height 3 part tripod diagonally though you need to take the head off and you can easily fit the full 50 pounds of luggage allowance while the dimensions suit all American carriers (and all international ones I know of)In use they have proved reliable, easy to maneuver and fairly tough (1 corner of 1 bag did get knocked in but a push from the inside restored it) and very very stable (presumably due to how low to the ground they are)Just remember which way is "up" so you don't dump the contents out when you open it.As an added bonus, they roll under the turnstiles for the MTA (NY city) subway and PATH - though they roll so well so need to be careful they don't get away from you when you do that.Can also be used to transport rack mounted gear so long as it is not more than 40cm (1' 4") deep or higher than 4UOverall very happy with them. They are not 'run over it with a truck' strong (just 'good for baggage handler' strong but that is the tradeoff you must pay for the lighter weight

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to maneuver, lightweight, looks really nice!
reviews.reviewText: We needed an actual square suitcase for a specific trip and found this one. Turns out - square is VERY hard to find. This is perfect, and as a bonus, it's a really nice suitcase. Got the teal, very pretty. Super easy to move around. Lightweight, with a great interior system. Comes with X-straps which work well, and a detachable packing cube. Just great in every way!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Huge win. Gorilla proof.
reviews.reviewText: Was looking for a good size suit bag to pack suits, tux, gowns and coats for a wedding in Mexico City. This fit the bill. Lots of room with a couple good zippered compartments. Super mobile with 360 degree wheels. Made it through gorilla bag handling gauntlet without a blemish. Like the look of it too. Arrived from Amazon pronto.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 15, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Tough and easy to wheel suitcase, love it so far.
reviews.reviewText: Took this suitcase with us on an extended trip. Wheels held up fine even while maneuvering 65 lbs inside it (our other suitcase did not and will need replaced). This one handled beautifully; super easy to lift, wheel, and pivot, making it seem super light-weight. I had no problem maneuvering it through multiple airports and uneven pavement with just one hand. Love how it has compartments and straps for holding items in place. Fits easily in the backseat of a car or in a trunk. Got many compliments on it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect in every way
reviews.reviewText: After 3 attempts I finally found the perfect carry-on suitcase. This one is the exact max size required by Alaska Air. I didn't want to risk it being too large for the overhead bins even by an inch. This one does expand if needed but I'm packing light for a long weekend trip. I love the color and the handle has a nice feel. Time will tell in regard to the wear/tear element but I am hopeful that as a Samsonite product it will hold up well. The wheels on these suitcases always seem questionable but I'm giving the benefit of the doubt until I put it to the test.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 20, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great luggage 5 stars
reviews.reviewText: We travel and use our luggage quite a bit. Had our last set for 5 years. I looked at a lot of different luggage on the internet and in person. This luggage is great. The "square" shape is unique and is a real plus. It fits easy in the car and everywhere else. It is easily identifiable at the airport. The luggage is durable, made well, the wheels roll perfectly. The inside and the various compartments were the final selling point for me. I found no interior in any other luggage as luxurious as this. The only negative is the zippers. I noticed some brands have these easy slide zippers and this does not. These are not so smooth. Lots more positives than this only negative. I purchased 2 large, 2 medium, and one of the small carry on size. Another plus is it's Moderate price. You will not find anything better. You will be very happy with this purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great roomy suitcase
reviews.reviewText: I wanted this size and shape so I could transport a large drum. It worked great and fit perfectly. The suitcase seems very durable. It does look a little battered on the outside after my trip but that's just rough airport handling. The important parts, the zipper and closure mechanism, seem good.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 11, 2023
reviews.reviewText: luggage is great but they sent wrong color and I don't have time to change.

Nothing to dislike. Samsonite is one of the best brands in luggage. I had my eyes set on this luggage for a l ong time and I finally have it. There are 2 pockets inside that's really practical for extra small clothings like socks and underwear that you want to grab without having to search the whole luggage. Built sturdy, zippers glide smoothly. BTW. This is a medium size strider. I'll probably purchase the large strider if availabe at Amazon.Thank you Samsonite.

reviews.reviewText: Arrêté de toujours oubliger des photots ou commentaires....mes etoiles suffisent
Es una maleta que cumple todo las expectativas, súper, tiene lo más cómodo posible y está distribuidos, lo recomiendo

reviews.reviewTitle: Excelente calidad, bonito color, elegante y funcional...
reviews.reviewText: La maleta se ve de excelente calidad. Después de ver bastantes otras opciones, la Samsonite Stryde fue la mejor opción. El precio es muy elevado pero con los descuentos del Hot Sale costó mucho menos. El material rígido se ve resistente y de buena calidad. Las llantas funcionales y prácticas. En el interior toda forrada de tela y cuenta con bolsa de plástico para artículos de baño, bolsa de malla para artículos pequeños, bolsa adicional con cierre en la tapa interior de la maleta y una pequeña bolsa de malla para meter objetos pequeños en el espacio libre que queda entre las barras de la agarradera. De hecho, la agarradera se me hizo que es un poco frágil aunque realmente es práctica por ser ancha y cuenta con 8 posiciones. A largo plazo veré si realmente no se rompe con el uso. Los cierres se notan de calidad superior y cuenta con sistema de candado práctico y fácil de poner la combinación. En general la calidad es superior, el diseño tambien y realmente está muy amplia para una maleta de éstas dimensiones, aparte de que se puede expandir algunos centímetros adicionales con sistema de cierres integrados. Sobre el color es como la ilustración un azul metálico grisáceo elegante y moderno con diseño de relieve vanguardista. Estoy contento con mi compra y creo que me servirá bastantes años. Súper recomendable
